The paper discusses a capstone course design for teaching agile software development methodologies, specifically Scrum and Kanban. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of lean principles, which could fall under the computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-category. The use of agile methodologies in industry is a current topic, which could fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the development artifacts created by students, which could fall under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper analyzes the perceptions of students, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
